Read My Lips... I don't want to be part of a mass murder. That is what your statement proposes. No thanks. We have issues in the Middle East, lets deal with them rationally and effectively with an understanding that every person was someone's child and all parents cry for their children. If killing is necessary we must focus on limiting it as much as possible to combatants. One of the generals who was involved in the Gulf war (sorry I don't remember his name) proposed a solution that involved targeting military sites with bombing campaigns, and at somepoint a surgical  strike to remove Sadaam. That to me is a more sensable approach. Remove the cancer, don't kill the body.<br>

